  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies the arguments used to clone or configure a typeface with variation, palette, and collection settings.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a ref struct that bundles the arguments used to clone or configure
a typeface via <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>. It lets you
specify the font collection index, a palette, palette overrides, and a variation design
position all in one value.

Because `SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct`, it cannot be stored on the heap. Set the
desired properties and pass the value directly to the API that consumes it.

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
    VariationDesignPosition = new ReadOnlySpan<SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate>(coords),
};

using var cloned = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
